<br>
Unrest was awesome and the most fun trains in the game.  In part, it was the availability of a rez (with so many clerics and paladins there the cr wasn't bad) and the great exp in zone that made the trains manageable.  A SoW went a long way with the short zone line.<br>
<br>
But the best part was that as a young Paladin, you learned the basic rule of EQ:  When you fight at a zone line, expect bad trains to happen right through you.<br>
<br>
