<br>
I do think many people learned how to deal with trains, bad pathing, flaky aggro (ooh, look, the bar AND the tower!), and general crowding isues in that zone. Now the place is pretty much empty of people who are the right level to hunt there, and it does seem to show in terms of how people at 53rd level deal with trains in places like Chardok. Hell, I've noticed a lot of people never even shout a warning. *shrug* <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=231378">Romidar Trueblade</a>
